  "response": "The cost of developing an iPhone app similar to Groupon can vary widely depending on several factors:\n\n1. App Complexity\n- Basic features: $20,000 - $50,000\n- Advanced features: $50,000 - $150,000+\n\nKey features would include:\n- User registration/login\n- Location-based deals\n- Search and filter functionality\n- Purchase and redemption system\n- Payment integration\n- Merchant dashboard\n- Reviews and ratings\n\n2. Cost Factors\n- Design complexity\n- Number of platforms (iOS only vs. iOS and Android)\n- Backend infrastructure\n- Third-party integrations\n- Ongoing maintenance\n\n3. Development Options\n- Freelance developers: $50-$150/hour\n- Local app development agency: $100-$250/hour\n- Offshore development: $25-$80/hour\n\n4. Estimated Total Cost Range\n- Simple version: $20,000 - $50,000\n- Mid-range app: $50,000 - $100,000\n- Complex, feature-rich app: $100,000 - $250,000+\n\nRecommendation: Get detailed quotes from multiple developers and clearly define your specific requirements to get an accurate estimate.",
